        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The plot uses three signal levels coded as red, blue and green from the strongest signal to the weakest. Consider the path at azimuth 135 degrees. As expected the signal strength decreases with distance due to diffraction loss. Tropospheric scatter loss then becomes the dominant propagation mechanism and the patter repeats. ",
        "bbox": [
            96,
            651,
            929,
            721
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "Pathloss 4.0 ",
