            928,
            954
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "An option is now provided to ignore tropospheric scatter loss in the diffraction and coverage modules. In the diffraction module, select Options - Diffraction Options and set the scatter method to do not calculate. ",
        "bbox": [
            63,
            85,
            591,
            156
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "image",
        "img_path": "images/9431b7ad2798eaf5f756b29869fa74ee129f543f44f8d3d979f2befc033dc901.jpg",
        "image_caption": [],
        "image_footnote": [],
        "content": "Diffraction Options\nScatter method Do not calculate\nTree type Dry bare trees\nFrequency (MHz) 150.00\nPolarization\nVertical\nHorizontal\nDivergence\nOK Cancel Help",
        "sub_type": "text_image",
        "bbox": [
            602,
            96,
            893,
            289
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In the coverage module, the options appears in the coverage calculation process under the “Calculate Diffraction loss section. ",
        "bbox": [
            63,
            290,
            473,
            345
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The results corresponding to the example above using the “Do not calculate” tropospheric scatter loss option are shown below. ",
